<br>
Does anyone know how damage is actually calculated?<br>
<br>
I saw an equation the other day that showed a rough estimate of how damage would be calculated, neglecting skill bonuses and item level over on Allakhazam, but I can't seem to find it anymore.<br>
<br>
The reason I ask is this: last night, I started a piercing defensive paladin since my 2-handed pally was busted; had trouble soloing greens at level 8. Obviously, 1-handed piercing weapons tend to be much, much faster than big old 2-handed slashers. However, at level 6, my new pally is using a 3.2 DPS main gauche and is tearing through mobs at a much higher rate than my 2-handed paladin at level 8, using a greatsword of the initiate (3.0 dps -- same mobs). Now, assuming I've distributed the skills in a relatively similar manner across both characters, the only real difference i can find is that my new paladin's weapons are much faster... and now that I think about it, I seem to remember weapon delay playing a factor in that damage equation. I was always under the impression that DPS was the stat by which a weapon was ultimately judged; afterall, it's damage per second: damage/delay, not damage per swing. So a weapon being swing twice as often for half the damage of another would have the exact same DPS.<br>
<br>
Is this true? Does delay play a role in damage? I prefer smaller, faster weapons, anyway, but I'm so in love of the look of a plate-clad female briton carrying a great axe... <p>--For every winner, there are dozens of losers. Odds are you're one of 'em. 
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugallatin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gallatin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/8/02 9:18:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=252.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://astro.temple.edu/~fmoffat/img/kitty6.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Damage calculations</span><hr size=1> &quot;but I'm so in love of the look of a plate-clad female briton carrying a great axe...&quot;<br>
<br>
I could have done without the fetish revelation, TMI, hehe.<br>
<br>
I'm so totally not a numbers person, I don't even know if this thread will help, but it's a shot. It's about assassins, but maybe there's some info in there that translates for you. My eyes glazed over reading it, hehe. <br>
<br>
I basically find something that cons nice and swing it until someone's dead. Sometimes it's me, usually it's them :-) But I understand some people actually enjoy being efficient, and enjoy figuring out the numbers behind the game. More power to you! <p><b>Gallatin</b><p>
<font size=1><a><a href=http://www.fridgemagnet.org.uk/kitchen.html>"Start cleaning up after your disgusting messy self, you utter, utter filthy bastard."</a></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unyssarainwhisper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyssa Rainwhisper</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/MiscImages/bluepawbullet.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/8/02 10:42:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=252.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/MiscImages/zidane.gif WIDTH=64 HEIGHT=64></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Damage calculations</span><hr size=1> I'm with Gallatin on this one.  While I can understand some people want actual numbers and statistics so they can be more efficient, I just aim, fire and hope it turns out in my favor.  It's really just a game to me and I don't sit there and bother with, well this mob wears this type of armor so I should do this or this to fight him or carry a bizillion weapons to hit different types of mobs with.  (I'm not saying that you're one of them but I do know several tanks that carries like 8 weapons with them to the point where they're so damn encumbered they can't move without my str buff.)<br>
<br>
Although it being efficient is part of strategy (which is essentially what you need to play DAoC), keep in mind that DAoC is still fairly new and most people don't really know all the jists of it yet.  Even the spoiler sites.  Heck even Sanya gives incorrect stats and info.  (She made some statement about mez time and such and was totally off.)<br>
<br>
Maybe you could get in on the Q&amp;A Grab Bag Sanya has over at Camelot Herald on Fridays.  She might have some answers. <p><CENTER>
